flow_state|05_Context|Flow State|Flow State describes the conditions under which attention becomes absorbed, effort feels steady, and progress starts to feel self-sustaining.|This domain looks at the conditions that make useful work easier to enter and easier to keep going across focus, ideas, movement, and conversation.|Read the ranked signals as likely flow conditions, not as a fixed identity. Lower-ranked signals are range to use deliberately, not weaknesses.|This is a ranked reading of the conditions most likely to help flow start, deepen, reset, and become useful.|active|flow_state::intro
06_Orientation
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|orientation_title|orientation_summary|score_shape_summary|rank_1_phrase|rank_2_phrase|rank_3_phrase|rank_4_phrase|status|lookup_key
flow_state|social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm|concentrated|social_exchange|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|Social exchange first|Start by looking at Social exchange. Bring in a way to pause, concentrate, and make the work more substantial when the work needs more range.|One signal is doing most of the work here. Social exchange is the clearest starting point for this result.|Your main route is conversation, feedback, and shared thinking.|What gives it depth: focused time with one demanding problem.|What adds energy: ideas, expression, and new angles.|What to use deliberately: movement, pace, and physical reset.|draft|flow_state::social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm::concentrated
07_Recognition
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|headline|recognition_statement|recognition_expansion|status|lookup_key
flow_state|social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm|concentrated|social_exchange|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|Flow starts through live exchange|You are most likely to find flow when conversation, feedback, or shared thinking helps the work become clearer.|This pattern often shows up when interaction gives the work energy and direction. You may think better while explaining, teaching, facilitating, debating, presenting, coaching, solving a problem with someone, or responding to live feedback. Deep Focus then helps you stay with what matters after the exchange has opened something up. Creative Movement brings in new angles so the conversation becomes more than simple reaction. Physical Rhythm becomes useful when social or mental energy needs a reset.|active|flow_state::social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm::concentrated
08_Signal_Roles
domain_key|signal_key|signal_label|rank_position|rank_role|title|description|productive_expression|risk_pattern|development_note|status|lookup_key
flow_state|social_exchange|Social Exchange|1|dominant|Social Exchange as the starting point|Social Exchange is where this pattern usually begins. Flow is most likely when conversation, feedback, teaching, facilitation, or shared problem-solving gives the work a live shape.|This can help you create clarity, energy, and momentum through exchange with other people.|The risk is continuing to talk, explain, or respond after the work now needs quiet focus, recovery, or a clear decision.|Use conversation to open the work, then notice when it is time to step back and choose what matters next.|active|flow_state::social_exchange::1
flow_state|deep_focus|Deep Focus|2|secondary|Deep Focus as the source of substance|Deep Focus helps this pattern become more than live response. It lets you stay with the important part after conversation has revealed what needs attention.|This can turn shared energy into careful work with depth, judgement, and follow-through.|The risk is moving too quickly from one exchange to the next before the useful insight has been developed.|Use focused time after the conversation to sort, refine, and make the work stronger.|active|flow_state::deep_focus::2
flow_state|creative_movement|Creative Movement|3|tertiary|Creative Movement as a way to widen the exchange|Creative Movement helps when the conversation becomes too reactive, narrow, or predictable. It brings new angles, reframing, and a less obvious way forward.|This can help shared thinking become more original and less dependent on the first response in the room.|The risk is adding more ideas when the useful move is to land the point, decide, or finish.|Use new angles to improve the exchange, not to keep it open longer than it needs to be.|active|flow_state::creative_movement::3
flow_state|physical_rhythm|Physical Rhythm|4|least_expressed|Physical Rhythm as useful reset|Physical Rhythm may not be your first way into flow, but it can help when conversation or mental energy becomes busy, draining, or overextended.|This can help you reset your state, lower the noise, and return with clearer attention.|The risk is staying in the exchange after your body is already showing that it needs a pause.|Use movement, pace, or a change of setting to reset before you keep responding.|active|flow_state::physical_rhythm::4
09_Pattern_Mechanics
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|mechanics_title|core_mechanism|why_it_shows_up|what_it_protects|status|lookup_key
flow_state|social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm|concentrated|social_exchange|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|Why exchange helps the work become clear|This pattern works by using live interaction to bring attention, energy, and meaning into the open. Once the exchange has revealed what matters, Deep Focus gives the work substance, Creative Movement adds new angles, and Physical Rhythm helps reset the system when the interaction becomes too busy.|It may show up because conversation gives the mind something active to respond to. The work can feel easier to enter when another person, group, audience, client, or live problem creates a real point of contact.|It protects shared clarity, useful momentum, and the ability to find meaning through response. The trade-off is that the exchange can continue after the work needs quiet attention or recovery.|active|flow_state::social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm::concentrated
10_Pattern_Synthesis
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|synthesis_title|gift|trap|takeaway|synthesis_text|status|lookup_key
flow_state|social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm|concentrated|social_exchange|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|Exchange that becomes focused clarity|You can create clarity, energy, and momentum through live exchange with other people.|You may keep talking, explaining, or responding after the work now needs quiet focus, recovery, or a clear choice.|Let the exchange open the work, then step back to focus and choose.|This pattern is strongest when live interaction creates a way into the work without becoming the whole process. Deep Focus helps you stay with the insight after the exchange ends. Creative Movement keeps the thinking from becoming only reactive. Physical Rhythm adds the reset that helps you return with clearer attention.|active|flow_state::social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm::concentrated
11_Strengths
domain_key|pattern_key|strength_key|priority|strength_title|strength_text|linked_signal_key|status|lookup_key
flow_state|social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm|strength_1|1|Creating clarity through exchange|You can often make progress by talking the work through, teaching it, testing it live, or solving it with another person. This helps unclear work become easier to see.|social_exchange|active|flow_state::social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm::strength_1
flow_state|social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm|strength_2|2|Turning shared energy into substance|After the exchange has opened something up, you can use focus to stay with the useful part. This helps the work become stronger than the conversation that started it.|deep_focus|active|flow_state::social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm::strength_2
flow_state|social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm|strength_3|3|Widening the conversation|When the exchange becomes too narrow, new angles can help you reframe the point. This keeps shared thinking from becoming only reaction or agreement.|creative_movement|active|flow_state::social_exchange_deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm::strength_3
